1. Insert the element normally in BST
2. Identify the node which make the tree unbalanced from bottom-up approach
3. Rotate the tree from the node using the 4 Rules

Abbrevations:
p -> parent node (from whose left and right are not balanced)
c -> child node
g -> grand child node under which the new item is inserted
t1 -> new inserted item


4 Rules:
1. If c and g both are on left-left case of p
then right rotate p

2. if c is left and g is on right of p then it is left-right case
then
a. make it in single line both c and g in left of p so left rotate c first
b. once done follow 1st rule and rotate p

3. if c and g both are on right of p then it is right-right case
and left rotate p

4. if c is on right of p and g is on left of c, then it is right-left case
a. right rotate c first
b. follow rule 3 and rotate p left